  <p class="paragraph1">
    Paragraph writing involves crafting a group of related sentences that
    develop a single main idea. A well-structured paragraph typically includes a
    topic sentence to introduce the main idea, several supporting sentences with
    details and examples, and a concluding sentence to summarize or transition.
    Proper structure and flow, along with a clear focus on one topic, help
    organize writing and guide the reader.
  </p>
